## How Cryotic works

Cryotic only comes from Excavation missions: every completed excavator pays a
flat **100 Cryotic** (1 per 1% of dig progress, so partial digs still count),
and the amount never scales with mission level — a dig on Earth pays the same
as one on Steel Path. A dig takes 100 seconds and burns four power cells
(20 seconds each), carried by specific enemies you kill near the site.

Because it's a mission payout rather than an enemy drop, only some boosters
touch it: a **Resource Booster doubles Cryotic** (silently — the in-mission
counter still shows 100) and a **Smeeta Kavat's Charm** proc doubles it too,
but Resource *Drop Chance* Boosters and blessings do nothing for it.

## Early game

**Everest** on Earth (Excavation) is the easiest farm and pays exactly as much
per dig as anything endgame. Keep one or two excavators running solo, feed
them power cells, and extract whenever you're done. **Tikal**, Earth's Dark
Sector Excavation, is a low-level Infested alternative with bonus credits.

## Late game

**Hieracon** on Pluto (Dark Sector Excavation) is the classic answer: Cryotic
is still 100 per dig, but the Dark Sector's +35% resource drop chance boosts
everything else the Infested drop, and reward rotations pay out Neo/Axi relics
and Endo on top. Bring Frost, Gara or Limbo to keep excavators alive, and a
Khora with Pilfering Strangledome if you want more power cells dropped.

The real ceiling, though, is an **endless Excavation Void Fissure**: every
200 Cryotic (two digs) cracks a relic, and each cracked relic grants a
stacking in-mission booster. The Resource Booster tier multiplies the Cryotic
payout itself — climbing from 1.25x to a 2x cap the longer you stay — and it
stacks with your account Resource Booster and Smeeta Charm, so long runs earn
300+ Cryotic per dig while banking prime parts and bonus relics for free.
Keep a single dig site active in fissures: Void Tear spawns are boosted when
only one excavator runs, keeping Reactant flowing.

